target: animals
validations:
  - name: species_data_completeness
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that all 10 species are defined with complete data: lion, elephant,
        penguin, monkey, giraffe, polar_bear, crocodile, parrot, dolphin, eagle.
        Each species must have: name, biome, cost, foodCostPerTick, spaceRequired,
        baseHappiness, breedCooldownTicks, color (hex), icon (single char), and
        visitorAppeal (numeric multiplier). No field may be missing or undefined.
        Values must match the species_table.md reference exactly.

  - name: happiness_formula
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the happiness calculation includes all factors: (1) biome match gives
        +20 for correct biome, -30 for wrong biome, (2) overcrowding penalty of -30
        per 100% over capacity, (3) hunger penalty of -0.5 * hunger value,
        (4) enclosure condition bonus of 0-10 based on condition percentage,
        (5) upgrade level bonus of +5 per level above base. Happiness must lerp
        toward the target value (not snap instantly) and be clamped to 0-100.

  - name: breeding_mechanics
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify breeding requires: (1) two animals of the same species in the same
        enclosure, (2) both at happiness >= BREED_THRESHOLD (80), (3) both with
        breedCooldown <= 0, (4) neither sick, (5) enclosure has remaining capacity.
        On success: a new animal is created in the same enclosure, both parents get
        their species breedCooldownTicks applied, and a toast notification fires.
        The per-tick breed chance is BREED_CHANCE_PER_TICK (0.02 = 2%).

  - name: death_and_removal
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that when an animal's health reaches 0, it is removed from the
        state.animals array, a notification toast is displayed with the animal's
        species and name, and a death sound effect is played. The removal must happen
        after all animals are updated for the tick (not mid-iteration). Verify that
        health decreases when the animal is sick (2x decay rate) or unhappy (<30
        happiness, 1x decay rate), and slowly regenerates when happiness >= 50.

  - name: purchase_validation
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the buyAnimal function checks: (1) species exists in the SPECIES table,
        (2) player has sufficient funds, (3) target enclosure exists, (4) enclosure
        biome matches species biome (unless Exotic Species research is unlocked),
        (5) enclosure has remaining capacity. The function must return a success/failure
        result with a reason string on failure. On success, the animal is added to
        state.animals and the cost is deducted from state.money.
